ont><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can a group exp grind in PoS?</span><hr size=1> Order of Perference:<br>
<br>
1. Frog Cave (where BoT zone in)<br>
<br>
2. Forest/Ocean/Desert Gaints<br>
<br>
3. Frogs and random mobs in Forest or Random mobs in Desert <br>
<br>
A back up healer is good for Gaints. A SK or Monk Puller is good. Did I say DPS? High DPS really helps a lot as mobs hit hard that you do not want to consume half of the cleric's mana bar for 1 mob.<br>
<br>
Anyone kill those Bees for Exp? What are they good for (exp or loots)? I was told they were tough and should not mess with them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leod>Leod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/03 3:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yup</span><hr size=1> Stay away from giants and you'll be fine. Go to Forest and work frogs, trees, bears and snakes (gotta get used to the pulling though, pathing can suck). go to desert and pull snakes, scorps, raiders, cacti, and storms (I'd leave storms alone though, their pathing really sucks bad).<br>
<br>
Or go into the center cave with the tornado and kill frogs. Enchanter highly highly suggested.... Frogs prolly best place IMO. Long respawn on them though....but there is a reason for that! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/03 3:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Yup</span><hr size=1> random desert mobs are really, really, really poor xp imo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I think youre better off killing giants &amp; having downtime than killing random desert mobs. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/mherlihy/img/gallerus.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
