<br>
5) Assorted trash all over the zone. I see lots of solo wizzies/druids kiting frogs in forest and zone in area, as an extra hazard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tenasi>Tenasi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/03 12:04 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bees best...</span><hr size=1> My notice in Storms was that random desert mobs dropped significantly in xp received at 64.  Used to be a sweet spot before that...now it's really just Diaku hunting for low dark blues. <p>Good travels,<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113095">Aurthur</a> / <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113135">Tenasi</a><br>
